<br>
I started EQ when a friend bought it for me on my birthday.  I had always loved roleplaying games like baldurs gate etc... I was good at them and loved em.  He thought I would like EQ and got it for me.<br>
<br>
Man it was awesome!  An entire new world with hundreds of people in it to interact with.  It was a new adventure each time I logged on.  I remember my first trip to freeport .. over a year ago.  My heart was beating and the boat trip was just awesome.  It was like I was leaving home and that was lvl 12.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I met some awesome people then .. warnin, luni, niffo, ronstad,talesinger.  sorry if I am leaving anyone out.  And then we decided to make a guild.  How awesome was that I thought to myself and I get to be an officer  ... COOL!!<br>
<br>
The guild grew and grew and I have made some great friends over the months .. gala, lluumm, inouva , glad, diora, vlieke, ara, tass, ord ... again sorry If I am leaving anyone out.  I loved this guild even though work and rl took most of my time I looked forward to getting on EQ. <br>
<br>
Well that all has changed .. it seems more like a chore than excitement getting on EQ.  I have debated this in my mind over and over and over and over.  I just hate to do this but I think this is for the best.  I am going to retire Taallon and quit EQ.<br>
<br>
I am going to join the ranks in the Dark Age of Camelot.  For now that really excites me.  I am only sad because I am leaving behind some really awesome people.  I can only thank EQ for allowing me to find you all and perhaps our friendship can extend beyond EQ.  <br>
<br>
I am going to be on tonite to see if anyone can start a mule in felwithe and I will donate all my plat and stuff I have to the guild.  (Man this is hard)  I thought this would be easier.<br>
<br>
If anyone would like to stay in contact my e-mail is bplakes07@yahoo.com.<br>
<br>
I have really enjoyed all your friendship and banter.  There have been times that I have laughed so hard that I was crying.  Those were great times that I will always remember. <br>
<br>
Victus  Fortis is a great guild that will grow stronger everyday.  With leaders like luni and gala it can do nothing but get better.  You all stick together and make everyone in EQ jealous that you are in such a great guild.<br>
<br>
Again I am on the albion section of DaOC on the galahad server.  Not sure of my name or anything yet.<br>
<br>
You all take care and I am going to miss you all!<br>
F <p><HTML>
